@startuml
!theme plain
title Disadvantage of "Update DB, then Delete Cache" Strategy

' === Participant Definition === '
actor "Request A (Read)" as A
actor "Request B (Write)" as B
entity "Cache" as Cache
database "Database" as DB

' === Execution Flow === '
A -> Cache : Cache miss
A -> DB : Sends request to read value from DB (current value = 1)
note right of A: This read operation takes time to complete...

' While A is waiting, B performs its write operation '
B -> DB : Update DB to 2
B -> Cache : Delete cache

note right of A #LightYellow
**Due to network/DB latency, A now receives the result**
of its earlier read command (the old value = 1).
end note
A -> Cache : Write old value (1) back to cache

' === Result Annotation === '
note over A, DB #LightPink
**Result: DB = 2, Cache = 1 -> Data inconsistency**
Request A (the read) writes stale data back into the cache
after Request B (the write) has already updated the DB and invalidated the cache.
end note

@enduml